title: Concern grows for missing 14-year-old | Central
text:
Police are becoming increasingly concerned over the whereabouts of missing teenager Aaron Magee.
The 14-year-old left his home on Austin Rise in Birmingham yesterday morning (18 February) and has not been seen since.
He is described as white, around 5ft 9ins tall and has shoulder length dark hair with a sweeping fringe.
He was last seen wearing a distinctive black hoodie that is printed with a heavy metal bandâ€™s name, Bullet for My Valentine.
Aaron is known to frequent the Kings Norton and Longbridge areas.
His family are extremely worried as they say this is really out of character for Aaron who has never been missing before.
Last updated Sun 19 Feb 2017 West Midlands birmingham
